27212722 FROM AMBROSE PELARGrs. Pelargus, Bellaria f0. H⁵. (Freiburg)

<sepe-Oct. 1532.)

[Epp. 2721-5 can be dated approximately-by comparison with Ep. 2728, which mentions the quarrel about Marius: and by the publication of the Epistolae Palaeonacoi (see 1. on). The order in which they stand in the Bellaria is plainly chronological. That this group of letters was written from Freiburg is proved by Erasmus‘ invitation to Pelargus to corne and discuss the matter at dinner.] ⁷
